<br>
I've never been to any part of ToV, so I have absolutely zero knowledge of how this would work.  I assume that the reason monks use the Eye of Zomm pulling trick is because they can feign death?<br>
<br>
If so, this &quot;nerf&quot; makes total sense to me now.  A wizard could have pulled NToV using Eye of Zomm (the spell) with the exception of not having feign death would make them one dead wizard.  Monks avoid that problem by feigning off the mobs or at least being able to take a few hits before the rest of the melees assist.  <br>
<br>
Is that the case, monks? <br>
<br>
If not, then I'm back to being confused. <p><A HREF=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45382><IMG SRC=http://members.shaw.ca/jlwestmoreland/sig.jpg></A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ueomerredmoon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eomer Redmoon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druzzil Ro Member</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/13/02 1:21:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846generaldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2171.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I think</span><hr size=1> The main advantages with it were that monks could pull from way farther away, so pathing had more of a chance of splitting the mobs up a bit, so they could feign, one mob would get back out of LoS on its way back, and the other would come after them when the monk stood back up. Not totally sure on that though, I am not a monk and have never played one.<br>
<br>
Also, it was a huge advantage to be able to aggro mobs, or more specifically a mob in a room of other mobs, w/o having to be in the LoS of any of them. Right there they would often get less mobs on a pull, and then add to the fact the distance factor, and it made pulls a lot easier.<br>
<br>
And while it sucks that a lot of monks paid incredible amounts for the item, I agree that it needed to be changed. VI designed ToV and other zones with FD in mind (they originally hadn't in old EQ, it hadn't occured to them it's HUGE implications, but instead of nerfing it, they accounted for it in the future). So now VI is supposed to go around designing encounters with Eye Of Zomm Gimp Pull tactics in mind? They let it slide with monks, because it gave them a clearly defined role in the game that no one else can come close to matching (although SK's do have FD, it's not nearly as good).<br>
<br>
They shouldn't have to balance the entire dynamics of zones with ONE item's effect in mind. That's why Donal's got nerfed, same with manastone. It's great that players envision really cool ways of doing things, but when it trivializes things (and it does, it allows a so-so monk to pull Ntov easily, whereas it takes a good monk to pull without), there has to be some sort of fix to it.<br>
<br>
Would you guys have been satisfied that they linked all mob's aggro together that spawned within a range of each other? So that they ALWAYS came, no matter what? Maybe they would have increased the difficulty of every raiding zone/area where the beads came in handy, to put the difficulty back to where it should be. I am sure that would make everyone happy. The zones are the same difficulty, but VI would have to divert lots of designers and programmers from more important things to bring the game balance in line, and the bazaar or whatever else would be pushed back a few more weeks/months.<br>
<br>
It really sucks that some people who paid massive amounts for this item are basically getting screwed, but on the other hand it was a needed nerf, and should have come a LONG time ago. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/udaw4888.showPublicProfile?language=EN>daw4888</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druzzil Ro Member</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/13/02 1:48:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846generaldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2171.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think</span><hr size=1> Although it was really fun to pull IK , and that GD see invis wyvern in NtoV to zonein..... it was way over powered.... for a mage/wizzard to be able to pull a mob solo, passed 10+ spawns, all of which are 60+ was not how NtoV was ment to be cleared........<br>
